purpose "Run the @PACKAGE_NAME@ program OBJECT-FILE and the given ARGUMENTs."
usage " [OPTION...] [OBJECT-FILE ARGUMENT...]"
versiontext "(c) SMite authors 1994-2019
This is free software: you are free to change and redistribute it
under the terms of the MIT/X11 License.
There is NO WARRANTY, to the extent permitted by law."

args "--unamed-opts --default-optional --no-handle-help --no-handle-version"

text "\
The exit status is the error code, or zero if execution HALTs normally.

The memory and stack are automatically grown as required.

To avoid an ARGUMENT being interpreted as an OPTION, add `--' before the
OBJECT-FILE.

Please report bugs to @PACKAGE_BUGREPORT@."

option "core-dump" c "dump core on memory exception" flag off
option "trace" - "write dynamic instruction trace to FILE" string typestr="FILE"
